t; letter-spacing:0.15pt">inquiry into the impact of the Fixed-Term Parliaments Act 2011 and how it </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.2pt">may affect the work of select committees in the year before the general </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">election.</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 75.6pt 0pt 54pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.3pt">As you will be aware, the Administration Committee does not scrutinise </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.4pt">legislation or Government policy. Our remit is to examine the services </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.2pt">provided by and for Members and visitors to Parliament by the House of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Commons. The Committee's programme of work is therefore less affected by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.15pt">the clear timetabling of the next general election than other departmental </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">select committees who may undertake pre-legislative scrutiny.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 75.6pt 1.8pt 54pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.4pt">However, certainty about the date of the next general election is very </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.1pt">welcome in terms of timetabling the Committee's business and helping the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">House prepare effectively for dissolution and ensure suitable new induction </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.3pt">arrangements for new Members in 2015. The Committee examined this </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">matter in some detail in its recent report, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">First Weeks at Westminster: </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.3pt">induction arrangements for new Members in 2015, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.3pt">which you may be </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">interested to consult.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.1pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><br /><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.1pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">19 December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>